        <div class="icon">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-search-check"><path d="m8 11 2 2 4-4"/><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"/><path d="m21 21-4.3-4.3"/></svg>
        </div>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Why should I trust your research?</strong></p>
    <p>We (<a href="https://www.propublica.org/people/byard-duncan">Byard Duncan</a> and <a href="https://www.propublica.org/people/ryan-gabrielson">Ryan Gabrielson</a>) are reporters at ProPublica. We’ve been reporting on car loans for more than a year. In that time, we reviewed thousands of pages of lawsuits and complaints, and we spoke to dozens of borrowers, consumer finance experts, auto lending specialists, former Exeter Finance employees and more. We do not profit in any way off of tools such as our loan extensions calculator.</p>
    <hr style="border: 0.5px solid var(--color-neutral-10); height: 1px; background: none;" />
